<title type="html"><![CDATA[Convert x Roms to 1 Multi Rom?]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=6415&amp;p=61910#p61910"><![CDATA[
You only need two switches, which give four combinations of settings. You could add a latch chip that's controlled by a menu, but you'd still have to patch one of the ROMs. If each ROM is small enough, you could put them all one one big ROM, and patch the code to run from different banks, thus using the SNES bank switching and not needing any extra hardware.<br /><br />Personally I'd stick with a pair of toggle switches; it's not like you have to change them very often.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=17">blargg</a> — Wed May 26, 2010 1:54 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
